02:29.106 --> 02:30.216
[screeches]

02:35.076 --> 02:39.125
WOMAN: ♪ The first Noel ♪

02:39.126 --> 02:43.215
♪ The angel did say ♪

02:43.216 --> 02:48.085
♪ Was to certain poor shepherds ♪

02:48.086 --> 02:52.145
♪ In fields as they lay ♪

02:52.146 --> 02:54.275
♪ In fields ♪

02:54.276 --> 02:56.215
You okay?

02:56.216 --> 03:00.175
WOMAN: ♪ Keeping their sheep ♪

03:00.176 --> 03:02.075
♪ On a cold winter's night ♪

03:02.076 --> 03:06.145
What's gonna happen?

03:06.146 --> 03:08.295
I don't know.

03:08.296 --> 03:12.195
But I promise you, as soon as I do,

03:12.196 --> 03:14.186
you are the first person I tell.

03:18.286 --> 03:22.165
What are you thinking about back there?

03:22.166 --> 03:26.265
Did you have Christmas
when you were a kid?

03:26.266 --> 03:28.295
Sort of.

03:28.296 --> 03:30.185
Why?

03:30.186 --> 03:32.205
A girl in my class has
an invisible ink pen.

03:32.206 --> 03:33.225
Hmm.

03:33.226 --> 03:36.215
It has a special light.

03:36.216 --> 03:41.155
You can only see the
writing when you shine it.

03:41.156 --> 03:45.095
Is that what you would
ask Santa for Christmas?

03:45.096 --> 03:49.255
WOMAN: ♪ Noel, Noel ♪

03:49.256 --> 03:54.095
♪ Born is the king ♪

03:54.096 --> 03:55.295
RICHARD: When you've taken your vows,

03:55.296 --> 03:59.125
and you turn your back on The Light,

03:59.126 --> 04:01.075
you are a Denier.

04:01.076 --> 04:02.145
EDDIE: I'm not a Denier.

04:02.146 --> 04:04.135
RICHARD: Did you not take vows, Eddie?

04:04.136 --> 04:06.075
EDDIE: I reject your labels.

04:06.076 --> 04:08.235
I am not signing this form.

04:08.236 --> 04:11.155
I know what happens when
you're labeled a Denier.

04:11.156 --> 04:13.255
You can't see your kids.

04:13.256 --> 04:16.255
I am seeing the kids, Sarah.

04:16.255 --> 04:19.084
Do not ask me to sign this.

04:19.086 --> 04:21.135
It's not up to Sarah, Eddie.

04:21.136 --> 04:24.285
- There are explicit instructions.
- Sarah...

04:24.286 --> 04:26.235
We'll handle this ourselves, Richard.

04:26.236 --> 04:28.255
Clarity requires forms to be signed.

04:28.256 --> 04:30.255
If we disregard the
system, things will only

04:30.256 --> 04:33.235
be more complicated later.

04:33.236 --> 04:37.255
The last time I checked,
you're 7R, Richard.

04:37.256 --> 04:39.235
I'm 8R.

04:39.236 --> 04:41.286
I think that I'm the authority here.

04:45.136 --> 04:47.285
[door buzzes]

04:47.286 --> 04:50.285
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

04:50.286 --> 04:57.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:57.086 --> 04:59.105
What's going on?

04:59.106 --> 05:01.075
My husband killed himself.

05:01.076 --> 05:02.125
I know.

05:02.126 --> 05:06.155
She gave me his journal... Sarah.

05:06.156 --> 05:11.115
It was full of madness.

05:11.116 --> 05:15.155
He was seeing things...

05:15.156 --> 05:17.085
The Ladder.

05:17.086 --> 05:19.195
He was determined to climb it.

05:19.196 --> 05:25.095
There are pages and pages
of crazy writings.

05:25.096 --> 05:29.115
"I tried to climb the ladder,
but every time I tried,

05:29.116 --> 05:31.175
"I kept burning my hands.

05:31.176 --> 05:36.135
"My hands are bloody and raw.

05:36.136 --> 05:39.175
Next time..."

05:39.176 --> 05:41.236
That was his last journal entry.

05:45.176 --> 05:49.115
"Next time I will climb The Ladder,

05:49.116 --> 05:52.175
even if it kills me."

05:52.176 --> 05:56.195
[sobbing]

05:56.196 --> 06:00.145
I wanted to die, too, when I read it.

06:00.146 --> 06:02.206
I tried to kill myself...

06:04.076 --> 06:06.296
[sobbing]

06:08.176 --> 06:10.176
But I couldn't go through with it.

06:13.296 --> 06:16.185
I've lost everything.

06:16.186 --> 06:18.166
This was my home.

06:22.136 --> 06:24.256
I know you don't take people back.

06:29.246 --> 06:31.175
RUSSEL: So come on, you got to tell me.

06:31.176 --> 06:34.095
Is Steve really coming?

06:34.096 --> 06:35.145
[laughs]

06:35.146 --> 06:37.155
Everyone is so pumped.

06:37.156 --> 06:40.075
It's gonna be the biggest day
in the history of The Movement,

06:40.076 --> 06:42.065
last three rungs.

06:42.066 --> 06:44.225
You know, I can throw a filter
on this thing if you guys want,

06:44.226 --> 06:45.225
make it a little warmer.

06:45.226 --> 06:47.155
Definitely want it warmer.

06:47.156 --> 06:49.255
We're gonna be doing a live
feed to Minnesota, San Diego.

06:49.256 --> 06:51.225
All right, well, I'll use
an amber filter, then.

06:51.226 --> 06:53.115
That's what we did for General Petraeus

06:53.116 --> 06:55.075
when he spoke at Town
Hall Veterans' Day.

06:55.076 --> 06:56.245
You kind of got his colors.

06:56.246 --> 06:59.145
General Petraeus colors, okay.

06:59.146 --> 07:00.265
Just gonna be you up there?

07:00.266 --> 07:02.276
Anybody else I need to worry about?

07:06.156 --> 07:09.155
<i>[somber music]</i>

07:09.156 --> 07:12.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:12.226 --> 07:15.085
[sighs]

07:15.086 --> 07:18.175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:18.176 --> 07:20.145
[sighs]

07:20.146 --> 07:26.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:26.276 --> 07:28.256
Holy shit.

07:34.116 --> 07:40.256
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:45.206 --> 07:46.295
Isn't the view incredible?

07:46.296 --> 07:48.205
Is that the Atlantic Ocean?

07:48.206 --> 07:49.295
Hudson River.

07:49.296 --> 07:51.165
It's beautiful.

07:51.166 --> 07:52.255
You should see the mountains in the fall

07:52.256 --> 07:54.165
when the leaves are a million colors.

07:54.166 --> 07:56.065
It's cold.

07:56.066 --> 07:57.205
Probably not so good for your dad

07:57.206 --> 07:58.255
to be out here too long.

07:58.256 --> 08:00.216
He hasn't been feeling well.

08:07.266 --> 08:11.095
I'm sorry, we just always
imagined a church wedding.

08:11.096 --> 08:13.245
- I don't believe in Jesus.
- Oh, don't say that.

08:13.246 --> 08:16.255
What has Jesus ever done for our family?

08:16.256 --> 08:18.175
So do you guys get to choose each other,

08:18.176 --> 08:23.155
or do they put you together
like those Moon People?

08:23.156 --> 08:24.245
Why'd you guys even come?

08:24.246 --> 08:27.115
You've already lost one daughter.

08:27.116 --> 08:29.205
I love this woman.

08:29.206 --> 08:30.295
And if you want me in your life,

08:30.296 --> 08:32.256
you will love her too.

08:38.176 --> 08:40.265
SARAH: When's the last
time you saw Silas?

08:40.265 --> 08:42.205
FELICIA: I haven't seen him in months.

08:42.206 --> 08:45.275
I've been calling him and calling him,

08:45.276 --> 08:50.065
and even when he disappears,
he usually calls me back.

08:50.066 --> 08:52.075
I have a bad feeling.

08:52.076 --> 08:57.295
And I've been seeing a snow
owl every morning on my walk.

08:57.296 --> 09:01.235
I, uh... I spoke to him on the phone

09:01.236 --> 09:04.125
after Cal took in the Hondurans.

09:04.126 --> 09:05.225
He was upset.

09:05.226 --> 09:07.115
He thought we had lost
sight of The Movement.

09:07.116 --> 09:08.205
That's why we flew out there.

09:08.206 --> 09:10.235
Do you think Silas came too?

09:10.236 --> 09:12.265
I mean, how else did the
Pachamama get on my desk?

09:12.266 --> 09:16.235
FELICIA: Maybe. Cal did
disappear that night.

09:16.236 --> 09:19.205
- What are you saying, Felicia?
- Nothing.

09:19.206 --> 09:21.115
SARAH: Yes, you were.

09:21.116 --> 09:22.285
I mean, that's a pretty big accusation.

09:22.286 --> 09:24.225
This is Cal we're talking about.

09:24.226 --> 09:25.276
[door opens]

09:29.226 --> 09:32.135
I should go.

09:32.136 --> 09:33.275
I was wondering if
you'd thought any more

09:33.276 --> 09:36.145
about Steve's wishes

09:36.146 --> 09:39.285
that you run this next phase
of The Movement with me.

09:39.286 --> 09:44.125
It's kind of hard for me to think about

09:44.126 --> 09:46.225
taking on more work.

09:46.226 --> 09:50.195
Are you okay?

09:50.196 --> 09:54.095
I just... I want you to
know I'm thinking of you.

09:54.096 --> 09:55.225
Please...

09:55.226 --> 10:00.145
Look, I know that, um,
we've had our clashes

10:00.146 --> 10:03.125
since I came back.

10:03.126 --> 10:08.275
That's only because you...
you get me so, um...

10:08.276 --> 10:13.085
It felt amazing to be close
to you the other night.

10:13.086 --> 10:14.235
But I think it's important to keep

10:14.236 --> 10:16.105
our relationship professional.

10:16.106 --> 10:19.116
- Yeah, for now.
- Always.

10:22.086 --> 10:24.256
- Well, you came to me.
- I know.

10:30.156 --> 10:34.085
So that was just about
getting your son back?

10:34.086 --> 10:36.105
No.

10:36.106 --> 10:37.235
I am sorry.

10:37.236 --> 10:40.175
Well, um...

10:40.176 --> 10:42.075
[chuckles]

10:42.076 --> 10:43.285
I do hope you'll heed Steve's wishes.

10:43.286 --> 10:49.075
You should be standing on
that stage with me on Friday.

10:49.076 --> 10:50.265
Where were you the night
that we took the vote

10:50.266 --> 10:52.246
on what to do with the Hondurans?

10:53.266 --> 10:56.265
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:56.266 --> 10:57.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:57.276 --> 11:00.195
Uh...

11:00.196 --> 11:01.245
You know where I was.

11:01.246 --> 11:05.175
Tell me.

11:05.176 --> 11:08.185
Um...

11:08.186 --> 11:12.185
I, uh...

11:12.186 --> 11:15.296
The day had gotten me very stressed...

11:19.216 --> 11:23.085
And I relapsed.

11:23.086 --> 11:26.185
I had a drink to, um,
take the edge off,

11:26.186 --> 11:29.095
and, uh...

11:29.096 --> 11:30.245
next thing I knew, it was next day,

11:30.246 --> 11:32.155
and I was lying in a
puddle of my own vomit.

11:32.156 --> 11:34.066
You know, I'm not proud of it.

11:36.246 --> 11:38.226
Why are you asking?

11:41.246 --> 11:49.226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:55.176 --> 11:59.205
Daddy's gonna be living
somewhere else from now on.

11:59.206 --> 12:04.105
Is he gonna bring The Light
to the other people?

12:04.106 --> 12:07.115
No, honey.

12:07.116 --> 12:08.205
I'm gonna live without The Light.

12:08.206 --> 12:11.165
But what is he if he has no Light?

12:11.166 --> 12:12.195
He's still our dad.

12:12.196 --> 12:13.265
That's right.

12:13.266 --> 12:17.135
And I love you guys more than anything.

12:17.136 --> 12:22.165
And whether or not I believe in
The Light won't change that.

12:22.166 --> 12:24.256
But are you gonna be
in The Garden with us?

12:29.106 --> 12:30.135
I don't know.

12:30.136 --> 12:32.065
It's okay, honey.

12:32.066 --> 12:35.265
You're still gonna see Daddy.

12:35.266 --> 12:38.225
But not in the future.

12:38.226 --> 12:42.255
Hey, nobody knows what's
gonna happen in the future.

12:42.256 --> 12:45.076
What matters is right now.

12:48.186 --> 12:52.185
Hey, Summer, it's okay.

12:52.186 --> 12:53.255
I'll be there.

12:53.256 --> 12:55.145
That's right.

12:55.146 --> 12:58.205
Hawk will be there, and
Daddy's gonna stay

12:58.206 --> 13:00.255
in a hotel in town
until he gets settled,

13:00.256 --> 13:05.165
and then you'll see him every Sunday.

13:05.166 --> 13:06.206
Come here.

13:09.166 --> 13:13.105
[sighs]

13:13.106 --> 13:16.065
I love you so much.

13:16.066 --> 13:18.125
Okay?

13:18.126 --> 13:20.066
It's gonna be okay.

13:21.086 --> 13:24.085
<i>[somber music]</i>

13:24.086 --> 13:28.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:28.246 --> 13:31.146
Happy birthday, kid.

13:33.256 --> 13:35.156
Come on, Summer.

13:36.176 --> 13:44.175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:44.176 --> 13:46.196
I love you guys.

13:47.216 --> 13:55.215
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:55.216 --> 13:58.196
[sobbing]

14:05.226 --> 14:07.285
I'm sorry.

14:07.286 --> 14:09.155
I'm so sorry.

14:09.156 --> 14:11.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:17.116 --> 14:20.115
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:20.116 --> 14:28.096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:31.196 --> 14:33.226
[sighs]

14:42.296 --> 14:45.276
[urinating]

14:46.296 --> 14:49.276
[hissing]

14:58.186 --> 15:01.166
[panting]

15:09.076 --> 15:10.206
What the fuck?

15:12.236 --> 15:15.216
[cell phone vibrating]

15:17.256 --> 15:19.136
Oh, shit.

15:22.116 --> 15:23.215
Hello?

15:23.216 --> 15:26.265
ABE: Hey, man, it's Sam, Sam Field.

15:26.266 --> 15:29.065
Hey, um, Sam.

15:29.066 --> 15:33.175
ABE: Listen, I-I-I just
wanted to call and apologize

15:33.176 --> 15:36.155
for the other day, you
know, being an asshole

15:36.156 --> 15:38.136
on the phone like that. I just...

15:40.226 --> 15:42.165
You've been good to me.

15:42.166 --> 15:44.135
No, uh...

15:44.136 --> 15:46.195
you're going through a
lot right now, Sam.

15:46.196 --> 15:48.245
ABE: Just checked my
daughter into the hospital.

15:48.246 --> 15:50.215
She's on a shit-load
of drugs right now.

15:50.216 --> 15:55.075
She on the last-ditch
attempt to close the valve

15:55.076 --> 15:57.166
before her open-heart surgery tomorrow.

16:02.106 --> 16:05.165
Listen, anyway, you know, I just
wanted to bury the hatchet.

16:05.166 --> 16:10.155
No, it's, um... no hatchet to bury.

16:10.156 --> 16:14.105
You, uh... you hang
in there, all right?

16:14.106 --> 16:17.085
ABE: Yeah, thanks.

16:17.086 --> 16:20.066
[panting]

16:25.106 --> 16:28.105
<i>[eerie music]</i>

16:28.106 --> 16:36.086
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:45.266 --> 16:47.156
[door buzzes]

16:56.246 --> 16:59.215
[exhales]

16:59.216 --> 17:01.105
Hungry?

17:01.106 --> 17:03.105
I just have a feeling that
Steve will come back.

17:03.106 --> 17:06.244
The last three rungs are
what we've been waiting for.

17:06.246 --> 17:08.185
What are the last three rungs?

17:08.185 --> 17:11.156
The entire map for our
spiritual development.

17:13.106 --> 17:14.115
Who's that?

17:14.116 --> 17:15.285
JOY: Alison Kemp.

17:15.286 --> 17:19.065
SHELBY: Her husband, Jason, trained me.

17:19.066 --> 17:21.105
Some of you may know of Alison Kemp.

17:21.106 --> 17:23.244
She is a Denier, and, yes,

17:23.246 --> 17:29.065
she waged a libelous war
against us on the Internet.

17:29.066 --> 17:30.285
But she has come back to us.

17:30.286 --> 17:32.225
And I know it is written in The Ladder

17:32.226 --> 17:38.195
that he who turns his back on
the Truth shall forever...

17:38.196 --> 17:41.145
walk in the world of shadows.

17:41.146 --> 17:45.215
But with the last three rungs...

17:45.216 --> 17:48.085
comes change.

17:48.086 --> 17:52.255
And this, uh... this unforgiving
tenet has been revisited.

17:52.256 --> 17:55.205
And now Steve asks us
to remember the words

17:55.206 --> 17:58.125
of another prophet of The
Light, the one who said,

17:58.126 --> 18:01.275
"Let he who is without sin

18:01.276 --> 18:04.065
cast the first stone."

18:04.066 --> 18:07.085
The Light has always asked us

18:07.086 --> 18:10.166
to be a Movement of love.

18:12.226 --> 18:17.115
And forgiveness is the
ultimate act of love.

18:17.116 --> 18:20.115
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

18:20.116 --> 18:28.106
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:57.286 --> 19:05.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:05.076 --> 19:08.246
SARAH: I saw that you were
on your post November 29th.

19:09.266 --> 19:11.125
Was I?

19:11.126 --> 19:12.295
It was the day we voted whether

19:12.296 --> 19:16.195
to turn over the Hondurans.

19:16.196 --> 19:18.235
Oh, yeah, sure, uh...

19:18.236 --> 19:20.265
Did you by any chance see Silas?

19:20.266 --> 19:22.146
No, definitely not.

19:26.166 --> 19:27.285
What about Cal?

19:27.286 --> 19:29.156
Did you see him?

19:32.226 --> 19:34.125
I don't remember.

19:34.126 --> 19:36.095
I'm just trying to
account for everybody's

19:36.096 --> 19:39.175
whereabouts that day, all the
upper rungs for the log,

19:39.176 --> 19:42.136
and Cal wasn't there
that day for the vote.

19:46.206 --> 19:48.205
What is it, Isiah?

19:48.206 --> 19:52.185
I did see him that night.

19:52.186 --> 19:53.285
Go on.

19:53.286 --> 19:57.245
He was drunk and falling,

19:57.246 --> 20:02.155
and I, uh... I helped him to his cab

20:02.156 --> 20:05.095
and then helped him get into bed.

20:05.096 --> 20:07.115
I promised him I wouldn't tell anyone.

20:07.116 --> 20:09.155
I won't tell a soul.

20:09.156 --> 20:12.155
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:12.156 --> 20:20.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:20.086 --> 20:21.225
[knock at door]

20:21.226 --> 20:24.095
May I come in?

20:24.096 --> 20:26.065
I was wondering if we could talk.

20:26.066 --> 20:29.195
Okay.

20:29.196 --> 20:32.275
Losing Sheila was unbearable.

20:32.276 --> 20:37.295
Then Sean joining this.

20:37.296 --> 20:41.235
But I was moved by your
leader, whoever he is,

20:41.236 --> 20:44.125
- the man in the cafeteria.
- Cal.

20:44.126 --> 20:47.255
Reminding me to not only forgive,

20:47.256 --> 20:51.145
but that we all need
to find our own ways

20:51.146 --> 20:54.205
to deal with tragedy and grief.

20:54.206 --> 20:59.235
And I'm so glad Sean found you.

20:59.236 --> 21:03.185
Anyway, this was mine.

21:03.186 --> 21:07.255
I don't know if you
like it, or if you even

21:07.256 --> 21:09.185
wear a veil when you get married here,

21:09.186 --> 21:12.245
but Sheila always used to
love dressing up in it

21:12.246 --> 21:16.185
when she was a little girl, and...

21:16.186 --> 21:19.146
- [voice cracks]
- I had planned to give it to her.

21:23.136 --> 21:26.205
Do what you like with it.

21:26.206 --> 21:27.255
Thank you, Mrs. Egan.

21:27.256 --> 21:30.285
Oh, call me Karen, please.

21:30.286 --> 21:32.145
Okay.

21:32.146 --> 21:35.145
<i>[gentle music]</i>

21:35.146 --> 21:42.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:42.226 --> 21:44.166
[door closes]

21:45.236 --> 21:49.235
<i>[monitors beeping]</i>

21:49.236 --> 21:51.065
[knock at door]

21:51.066 --> 21:53.225
Hey, Sam.

21:53.226 --> 21:56.295
Eddie.

21:56.296 --> 21:58.255
Hey, how did you find me, man?

21:58.256 --> 22:00.145
Well, you said your, uh...

22:00.146 --> 22:02.085
your baby was having heart surgery

22:02.086 --> 22:05.185
at St. Michael's, so
I thought I would...

22:05.186 --> 22:08.135
Hi, you must be Susan.

22:08.136 --> 22:11.205
Yes, I am, Susan.

22:11.206 --> 22:14.135
And you must be the guy
at that Meyer place

22:14.136 --> 22:16.225
- my husband's been talking to.
- Yeah.

22:16.226 --> 22:18.175
How's Lucy doing, Mrs. Gaines?

22:18.176 --> 22:19.235
Oh, she's fine.

22:19.236 --> 22:21.235
She's getting a little sleepy.

22:21.236 --> 22:24.255
It's my maiden name.

22:24.256 --> 22:28.185
Hey, Eddie, Eddie, Eddie.

22:28.186 --> 22:31.135
Hey, you know, thanks for coming.

22:31.136 --> 22:32.216
It's really good of you.

22:35.256 --> 22:37.205
It's just not a good time.

22:37.206 --> 22:41.105
Oh, hey, no worries.

22:41.106 --> 22:44.275
I just wanted to come and
wish you both well in person

22:44.276 --> 22:49.196
and let you know that I
am leaving The Movement.

22:51.276 --> 22:54.175
- You're leaving?
- Yeah.

22:54.176 --> 22:57.175
You know, just in case
you were still looking

22:57.176 --> 22:59.205
for someone to talk to over there.

22:59.206 --> 23:04.135
Why? Is your whole family leaving?

23:04.136 --> 23:07.235
Uh, no.

23:07.236 --> 23:10.235
Just... just me.

23:10.236 --> 23:13.205
I've been...

23:13.206 --> 23:15.165
struggling with my faith

23:15.166 --> 23:18.106
for a while now.

23:19.236 --> 23:21.295
I'm sorry, I should
have told you sooner.

23:21.296 --> 23:23.225
No.

23:23.226 --> 23:26.096
Well, thanks, man.

23:31.166 --> 23:35.255
Hey.

23:35.256 --> 23:39.265
Light, who gives and takes life,

23:39.266 --> 23:43.105
watch over this baby, Lucy Field,

23:43.106 --> 23:45.215
this innocent soul.

23:45.216 --> 23:48.155
Use your warmth to heal her heart

23:48.156 --> 23:52.155
so that she doesn't have to
have this operation tomorrow.

23:52.156 --> 23:56.296
We look to you for strength,
guidance, and hope.

24:05.166 --> 24:07.106
I thought you didn't believe.

24:10.276 --> 24:12.176
Can't hurt.

24:29.256 --> 24:31.206
Happy birthday.

24:35.076 --> 24:36.256
Are you leaving school?

24:39.246 --> 24:42.135
<i>[somber music]</i>

24:42.136 --> 24:44.165
You're taking your vows?

24:44.166 --> 24:46.146
[bell rings]

24:49.156 --> 24:56.065
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:56.066 --> 24:58.146
Hawk...

25:02.296 --> 25:10.296
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:37.076 --> 25:42.295
MAN: ♪ O come, all ye faithful ♪

25:42.296 --> 25:47.285
- [bell dinging]
- ♪ Joyful and triumphant ♪

25:47.286 --> 25:52.275
♪ O come ye, O come ye ♪

25:52.276 --> 25:54.185
Hey.

25:54.186 --> 25:55.235
Watch where you're going.

25:55.236 --> 25:56.285
Sorry.

25:56.286 --> 25:59.266
[distorted traffic sounds]

26:01.266 --> 26:04.185
[distorted indistinct chatter]

26:04.186 --> 26:05.185
MAN: Watch where you're going.

26:05.186 --> 26:08.195
[distorted car horn honks]

26:08.196 --> 26:11.195
[distorted panting]

26:11.196 --> 26:14.176
[heartbeat echoing]

26:16.206 --> 26:17.275
- Yeah.
- No.

26:17.276 --> 26:19.115
But you've got it?

26:19.116 --> 26:21.285
Yeah, I think it would probably be...

26:21.286 --> 26:23.225
- back there, maybe.
- [door closes]

26:23.226 --> 26:26.065
- Okay.
- Diagonally, straight back.

26:26.066 --> 26:27.255
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

26:27.256 --> 26:30.236
[Eddie continues to pant]

26:36.096 --> 26:39.095
<i>[quick drum beats]</i>

26:39.096 --> 26:43.095
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:43.096 --> 26:46.065
<i>[eerie music]</i>

26:46.066 --> 26:48.115
- Can I help you?
- [gasps]

26:48.116 --> 26:51.255
- Sir?
- [panting]

26:51.256 --> 26:53.166
Do you need help?

26:57.076 --> 27:00.255
So then Sarah asked me if
I'd seen you that night.

27:00.256 --> 27:02.135
She did.

27:02.136 --> 27:04.295
And I told her exactly
what you said to say.

27:04.296 --> 27:06.285
Thanks, Isiah.

27:06.286 --> 27:09.175
I mean, you're doing The
Movement a great service.

27:09.176 --> 27:12.235
Someday I'll be able to tell you
why I had to leave that night,

27:12.236 --> 27:14.125
but I can't now.

27:14.126 --> 27:16.215
Hey, you don't have to
explain anything to me.

27:16.216 --> 27:18.195
All right, well, you'll
be rewarded for this

27:18.196 --> 27:20.276
in the next phase of The Movement.

27:25.126 --> 27:28.125
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:28.126 --> 27:34.195
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:34.196 --> 27:37.195
[car engine rumbles]

27:37.196 --> 27:43.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:43.146 --> 27:47.245
It's me.

27:47.246 --> 27:55.226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:57.126 --> 27:59.176
[sighs]

28:02.296 --> 28:05.185
[exhales sharply]

28:05.186 --> 28:07.166
What do you want, Eddie?

28:11.136 --> 28:13.245
I, um...

28:13.246 --> 28:15.255
I think something's wrong with me.

28:15.256 --> 28:17.115
I'm aware.

28:17.116 --> 28:20.115
[inhales deeply, exhales sharply]

28:20.116 --> 28:23.096
No, I think something is...

28:25.146 --> 28:29.135
Really wrong with me.

28:29.136 --> 28:34.106
Ever since I left, I
have been seeing things.

28:37.166 --> 28:39.145
Seeing things?

28:39.146 --> 28:42.255
Yeah, it's like I am on the medicine,

28:42.256 --> 28:46.095
but I am stone cold sober.

28:46.096 --> 28:49.295
What kind of things?

28:49.296 --> 28:51.276
Um...

28:55.086 --> 28:57.105
Snakes.

28:57.106 --> 28:58.185
- Snakes?
- Yeah.

28:58.186 --> 28:59.295
A dead bird.

28:59.296 --> 29:04.155
The hallways at the
retreat center in Cuzco.

29:04.156 --> 29:07.255
I saw the door where I saw Doc was dying

29:07.256 --> 29:10.186
- when I was on the medicine.
- You saw Doc dying.

29:12.276 --> 29:14.115
What about The Ladder?

29:14.116 --> 29:16.225
Do you see The Ladder?

29:16.226 --> 29:17.295
No.

29:17.296 --> 29:22.065
Do you think that I... am going crazy?

29:22.066 --> 29:25.245
I mean, is this a psychotic break?

29:25.246 --> 29:28.205
I think you're having visions, Eddie.

29:28.206 --> 29:30.225
You have to find out what they mean.

29:30.226 --> 29:32.165
How am I supposed to
find out what they mean?

29:32.166 --> 29:35.126
The Light is trying to
communicate with you.

29:38.176 --> 29:42.085
Richard, get out.

29:42.086 --> 29:43.135
Eddie...

29:43.136 --> 29:45.295
Get out of the fucking car.

29:45.296 --> 29:48.175
I knew you would make
this about The Light.

29:48.176 --> 29:50.185
I am losing my fucking mind here.

29:50.186 --> 29:53.255
They won't go away until you
find what they're asking of you.

29:53.256 --> 29:55.176
Get out!

29:59.216 --> 30:02.196
[car engine starts]

30:04.296 --> 30:07.236
- [shouts]
- And if you don't find out...

30:10.116 --> 30:11.296
- [normal voice]
- They'll destroy you.

30:20.136 --> 30:23.275
Everything okay?

30:23.276 --> 30:25.236
I'm not a good person.

30:29.176 --> 30:32.165
Where's this coming from?

30:32.166 --> 30:33.266
I'm like you.

30:37.076 --> 30:39.186
People hurt us, and we got broken.

30:41.116 --> 30:43.225
We can't be fixed.

30:43.226 --> 30:46.206
I don't believe that's true.

30:48.276 --> 30:51.265
Sean's mother gave this to me.

30:51.266 --> 30:54.115
For his bride, that's
who it should be for.

30:54.116 --> 30:57.195
You are his bride.

30:57.196 --> 31:01.126
I'm someone who will try
to be good to him...

31:02.276 --> 31:04.236
And love him.

31:07.156 --> 31:12.065
But I'll always want
something dark near me...

31:12.066 --> 31:13.246
inside me.

31:23.276 --> 31:28.096
That's why it's so good
you're marrying him.

31:33.096 --> 31:37.185
We need to surround
ourselves with forces

31:37.186 --> 31:40.125
that will bring out the goodness

31:40.126 --> 31:42.215
that we are capable of.

31:42.216 --> 31:44.296
But I still want you.

31:47.076 --> 31:49.295
I want to be held by
someone who knows me,

31:49.296 --> 31:52.236
really knows me.

31:54.156 --> 31:56.255
All my corners.

31:56.256 --> 31:59.255
<i>[urgent music]</i>

31:59.256 --> 32:07.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:42.226 --> 32:45.206
[car door opens, closes]

32:49.256 --> 32:53.135
Where is, uh... where's Summer?

32:53.136 --> 32:54.225
She's at my parents'.

32:54.226 --> 32:56.085
I had to work late.

32:56.086 --> 32:59.095
Should be dropping her off any moment.

32:59.096 --> 33:00.295
All right, well, I, uh, have something

33:00.296 --> 33:02.165
that I want to give to her.

33:02.166 --> 33:04.095
My family's coming for dinner, Eddie.

33:04.096 --> 33:05.295
Why don't you just give me
what you have for Summer,

33:05.296 --> 33:07.255
and I'll give it to her.

33:07.256 --> 33:09.165
I want to give it to her.

33:09.166 --> 33:11.175
It'll only upset her
to see you right now.

33:11.176 --> 33:13.155
She's my fucking kid, Sarah.

33:13.156 --> 33:15.085
Just go home and get some sleep.

33:15.086 --> 33:16.235
You see, that's the problem here.

33:16.236 --> 33:19.255
I don't have a fucking
home anymore, okay?

33:19.256 --> 33:21.235
This was my home.

33:21.236 --> 33:23.065
You were my home.

33:23.066 --> 33:25.135
My family's here.

33:25.136 --> 33:27.095
I'll call you tomorrow.

33:27.096 --> 33:29.295
Daddy!

33:29.296 --> 33:31.225
Hey.

33:31.226 --> 33:34.235
NICOLE: All right, you guys
go on inside. Come on.

33:34.236 --> 33:37.145
Hey, I got you something.

33:37.146 --> 33:38.225
Time to go, Eddie.

33:38.226 --> 33:43.145
Come on, Eddie.

33:43.146 --> 33:45.235
Hey, what did your daddy give you?

33:45.236 --> 33:47.065
Let's go inside and play, okay?

33:47.066 --> 33:48.245
Come on.

33:48.246 --> 33:50.226
Go hang with the kids
until you feel up for us.

33:58.146 --> 34:01.145
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:01.146 --> 34:07.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:07.136 --> 34:09.235
[car engine starts]

34:13.275 --> 34:16.205
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:16.206 --> 34:18.195
You did the right thing, sweetie.

34:18.196 --> 34:20.094
It'll be better soon

34:20.096 --> 34:24.295
and you will feel good about this.

34:24.295 --> 34:26.114
- Really?
- Yes.

34:26.116 --> 34:27.264
- It's gonna feel good?
- Yes.

34:27.266 --> 34:29.185
Does it feel good that
you haven't seen Tess

34:29.186 --> 34:31.275
for 15 years, huh?

34:31.275 --> 34:33.235
Is it good that my kids
are gonna grow up...

34:33.235 --> 34:35.235
- [voice cracks]
- Without a father?

34:35.235 --> 34:38.074
Really?

34:38.076 --> 34:40.065
- And what about me?
- [crying]

34:40.065 --> 34:41.094
You know, I loved him.

34:41.096 --> 34:44.185
I love him.

34:44.186 --> 34:48.175
So fuck you, it's gonna feel good.

34:48.176 --> 34:50.156
Fuck all of you.

35:00.126 --> 35:03.106
<i>[horn blows]</i>

35:06.086 --> 35:09.095
<i>[upbeat violin music]</i>

35:09.096 --> 35:17.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:31.276 --> 35:34.225
<i>[phones ringing]</i>

35:34.226 --> 35:35.225
Oh, God.

35:35.226 --> 35:36.255
Hey, is everything okay?

35:36.256 --> 35:38.105
Yes, I have news.

35:38.106 --> 35:39.105
Well, how do you have news?

35:39.106 --> 35:40.175
She just went into surgery.

35:40.176 --> 35:41.175
We ran some tests this morning.

35:41.176 --> 35:42.265
Why?

35:42.266 --> 35:45.125
It's procedure before an operation.

35:45.126 --> 35:48.205
And we found that the
PDA had cleared itself.

35:48.206 --> 35:54.195
Do you understand? The
vessel closed on its own.

35:54.196 --> 35:55.285
Wait a minute, are you saying

35:55.286 --> 35:57.215
that she doesn't need the surgery?

35:57.216 --> 36:00.146
Yes, that is what I'm saying.

36:04.246 --> 36:06.295
We had her on prostaglandin
inhibitors...

36:06.296 --> 36:08.275
indomethacin, intravenous ibuprofen.

36:08.276 --> 36:13.105
Maybe it was just the dose she
needed to close the vessel.

36:13.106 --> 36:15.175
Thank you.

36:15.176 --> 36:17.285
Thank you.

36:17.286 --> 36:19.175
Of course.

36:19.176 --> 36:21.125
We'll get Lucy back up to her room.

36:21.126 --> 36:24.225
You can check her out.

36:24.226 --> 36:28.095
Happy holidays.

36:28.096 --> 36:29.236
It's gonna be okay.

36:31.186 --> 36:34.166
[exhales]

36:35.186 --> 36:38.185
<i>[gentle music]</i>

36:38.186 --> 36:40.096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:53.236 --> 36:55.225
- Hey.
- Can I come in?

36:55.226 --> 36:57.245
Well, I'm just... I'm just
working on something.

36:57.246 --> 37:00.195
It's kind of private.

37:00.196 --> 37:04.165
I just, um...

37:04.166 --> 37:07.115
I came to say yes.

37:07.116 --> 37:09.245
Yes?

37:09.246 --> 37:13.115
I want to stand beside you on Friday.

37:13.116 --> 37:15.285
I want to take The Movement
to the next generation...

37:15.286 --> 37:17.136
with you.

37:18.226 --> 37:22.155
Um...

37:22.156 --> 37:24.106
I'm so glad, Sarah.

37:27.256 --> 37:31.126
Together we're gonna
make this thing grow.

37:34.136 --> 37:36.265
Uh, I'll find you later,

37:36.266 --> 37:39.146
and we'll discuss everything.

37:46.066 --> 37:49.065
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:49.066 --> 37:56.296
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:22.086 --> 38:25.085
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:25.086 --> 38:32.165
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:32.166 --> 38:35.115
- [gasps]
- [hisses]

38:35.116 --> 38:37.285
[whimpers]

38:37.286 --> 38:40.265
[electricity buzzes]

38:40.266 --> 38:43.246
[panting]

39:03.106 --> 39:06.086
[bells tolling]

39:11.076 --> 39:13.185
CAL: Today we have much to celebrate.

39:13.186 --> 39:17.155
December 29th will forever
be marked as the day

39:17.156 --> 39:20.145
our book was finished, and the day

39:20.146 --> 39:22.285
our lives truly began.

39:22.286 --> 39:25.266
[cheers and applause]

39:27.256 --> 39:30.065
What could be more symbolic of new life

39:30.066 --> 39:31.285
than the three services
that Sarah and I

39:31.286 --> 39:34.095
will perform today?

39:34.096 --> 39:38.065
Recommitment of a Denier,

39:38.066 --> 39:40.275
a wedding,

39:40.276 --> 39:43.255
and the taking of vows.

39:43.256 --> 39:46.255
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

39:46.256 --> 39:50.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:50.146 --> 39:53.085
Please forgive this Denier.

39:53.086 --> 39:56.175
Forgive her wanderings.

39:56.176 --> 40:00.235
And allow The Light back into her soul.

40:00.236 --> 40:02.235
[echoing]

40:02.236 --> 40:06.155
Let the bonding of these
hands be a symbol

40:06.156 --> 40:08.235
of the bond that you
have to each other.

40:08.236 --> 40:11.125
[echoing]

40:11.126 --> 40:13.155
CAL: Do you accept The
Light into your heart?

40:13.156 --> 40:14.285
HAWK: I do.

40:14.286 --> 40:17.205
Do you vow never to turn
your back on the message

40:17.206 --> 40:20.255
no matter what darkness may
creep into your heart?

40:20.256 --> 40:22.165
HAWK: I do.

40:22.166 --> 40:24.275
[echoing]

40:24.276 --> 40:27.125
SARAH: Wear this as a reminder

40:27.126 --> 40:30.295
that there is one all-seeing
force that sees everything

40:30.296 --> 40:34.085
that we do, that all
of our actions matter,

40:34.086 --> 40:36.275
and we are never alone.

40:36.276 --> 40:39.256
[applause]

40:41.176 --> 40:43.265
I can't believe how many came.

40:43.266 --> 40:45.156
It's only the beginning.

40:47.266 --> 40:49.255
Next year we'll need a
bigger gathering house.

40:49.256 --> 40:51.265
[both chuckle]

40:51.266 --> 40:53.175
There's only one question

40:53.176 --> 40:56.185
that's been on everyone's
lips for days.

40:56.186 --> 40:57.295
Is Steve coming?

40:57.296 --> 41:00.075
[laughter]

41:00.076 --> 41:01.175
Well, he's here.

41:01.176 --> 41:05.145
[all gasp]

41:05.146 --> 41:07.265
Dr. Steven Meyer, our founder,

41:07.266 --> 41:10.185
our interpreter, and our guardian

41:10.186 --> 41:13.275
has decided that the
time has come for him

41:13.276 --> 41:16.265
to transcend his earthly form

41:16.266 --> 41:19.185
and become pure Light.

41:19.186 --> 41:20.295
[murmuring]

41:20.296 --> 41:22.255
I wept for days when he told me.

41:22.256 --> 41:27.075
I begged him, begged him not to go.

41:27.076 --> 41:28.295
But most of you know
he was a father to me.

41:28.296 --> 41:32.215
- He was my only real parent.
- [crying]

41:32.216 --> 41:37.115
Then Steve reminded me that he's not...
he's not gone.

41:37.116 --> 41:38.205
[chuckles]

41:38.206 --> 41:41.185
In fact, he's with us more than ever.

41:41.186 --> 41:43.145
He's with us always.

41:43.146 --> 41:47.295
Because every day as we rise and...
and see the sun

41:47.296 --> 41:52.225
and feel its warmth,
every day when we look

41:52.226 --> 41:57.205
to The Light, Steve is
looking back at us.

41:57.206 --> 42:00.225
Steve promised a miracle,

42:00.226 --> 42:05.225
and this is his miracle for us.

42:05.226 --> 42:10.075
Because he loves us so very much.

42:10.076 --> 42:15.275
He has asked that Sarah
and I assume his post.

42:15.276 --> 42:20.275
And, together, we be
Guardians of The Light.

42:20.276 --> 42:24.225
I for one know that I will try my best

42:24.226 --> 42:28.185
to be half the leader he was.

42:28.186 --> 42:31.166
[cheers and applause]

42:44.116 --> 42:47.125
[folk music]

42:47.126 --> 42:55.106
♪ ♪

43:03.166 --> 43:06.085
Hey, Summer.

43:06.086 --> 43:08.285
What's going on?

43:08.286 --> 43:12.256
Daddy got me an invisible
ink pen for Christmas.

43:45.116 --> 43:46.165
Congratulations, Sarah.

43:46.166 --> 43:48.145
Oh, thank you, Meera. Thank you.

43:48.146 --> 43:50.105
There's somebody at the front gate.

43:50.106 --> 43:51.215
He's a real pain in the ass,
says he needs to see you.

43:51.216 --> 43:53.095
- Um...
- I can call the cops.

43:53.096 --> 43:54.205
No, no, that's okay.

43:54.206 --> 43:55.206
I'll take care of it.

43:58.116 --> 43:59.225
Can I help you?

43:59.226 --> 44:02.285
Yeah, I want to talk to my daughter.

44:02.286 --> 44:03.275
What's your daughter's name?

44:03.276 --> 44:05.185
She's Mary Cox,

44:05.186 --> 44:07.205
and the last time I was
here, that fucker Cal,

44:07.206 --> 44:09.195
